                <div class="div-line"></div>
                  <h2 class="subheading">1.Overview & Positioning</h2>
            
            <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Vitara Brezza</h3>
            <p>Brezza is Maruti's flagship sub-4m SUV, powered by a 1.5L K-Series petrol engine with SHVS mild-hybrid tech. It also offers an S-CNG version. Known for its strong real-world efficiency, Maruti's immense service network, and fuel-focused practicality.</p>

            <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Venue</h3>
            <p>Venue, Hyundai's popular sub-compact SUV, is available in three powertrains: 1.2L NA petrol, 1.0L turbo petrol, and 1.5L diesel. The updated 2024 model brings fresh styling, advanced connected features (Bluelink), and premium equipment across trims.</p>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">2.Engine & Performance</h2>
            
            <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine:</span> 1,462cc K-Series DualJet petrol with Dual VVT + SHVS</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power:</span> ~102PS@6,000rpm</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Torque:</span> ~137Nm@4,400rpm</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 5-speed manual, 6-speed torque converter AT</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Special Fuel:</span> S-CNG MT variant available</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Venue</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.2L NA petrol:</span> 1,197cc Kappa MPI, 83PS, 113.8Nm - 5-speed MT</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.0L turbo petrol:</span> 998cc Kappa T-GDi, 118PS, 172Nm - 6-speed MT / 7-speed DCT</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">1.5L diesel:</span> 1,493cc U2 CRDi, 114PS, 250Nm - 6-speed MT</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="verdict">
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Key Takeaway:</span> Brezza's NA petrol with mild-hybrid provides smooth, linear output and excellent mileage. Venue offers powertrain diversity: the turbo petrol excels in mid-range punch; diesel delivers high torque for heavy duty use.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">3.Fuel Efficiency (ARAI)</h2>
            
            <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Petrol MT: 17.38kmpl</li>
                <li>Petrol AT: 19.8kmpl</li>
                <li>S-CNG MT: 25.51km/kg</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Venue</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>1.2L petrol: ~18.3kmpl</li>
                <li>Turbo petrol: ~18.3kmpl (combined)</li>
                <li>Diesel: ~23.4kmpl</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="verdict">
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Verdict:</span> Brezza excels on petrol efficiency with mild-hybrid and CNG options. Venue's diesel closely rivals but petrol models are mid-tier comparable.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">4.Dimensions & Practicality</h2>
            <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                <table class="comparison-table-content">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th class="text-center">Specification</th>
                            <th class="text-center">Brezza</th>
                            <th class="text-center">Venue</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr class="compare-head-text">
                            <td>Length</td>
                            <td>3,995mm</td>
                            <td>3,995mm</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Width</td>
                            <td>1,790mm</td>
                            <td>1,770mm</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="compare-head-text">
                            <td>Wheelbase</td>
                            <td>2,500mm</td>
                            <td>2,500mm</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Ground Clearance</td>
                            <td>198mm</td>
                            <td>~195mm</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="compare-head-text">
                            <td>Boot Space</td>
                            <td>328L</td>
                            <td>350L</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Fuel Tank Capacity</td>
                            <td>48L</td>
                            <td>45L</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <p><span class="font-weight-700">Insight:</span> They share nearly identical footprint. Venue offers a larger boot, while Brezza boasts slightly better ground clearance and marginally larger fuel tank—beneficial on long drives.</p>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">5.Safety & Ratings</h2>
            
            <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Equipped with 6 airbags, ABS + EBD, ESP with Hill-Hold Assist, ISOFIX, reverse sensors, Suzuki TECT built-in body structure</li>
                <li>No current GNCAP rating for latest model</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Venue</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Features across all trims: 6 airbags, ABS with EBD, ESC, HAC, VSM, tyre pressure monitoring, rear camera, parking sensors, electrochromic IRVM on high trims</li>
                <li>Hyundai's Bluelink helps with SOS/emergency services</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="verdict">
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Conclusion:</span> While both are well-equipped, Venue offers more advanced driver aids and active safety systems like ESC, VSM, and HAC standard across line-up.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">6.Features & Comfort</h2>
            
            <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>9″ SmartPlay Pro+ touchscreen with wireless Android Auto/Apple CarPlay</li>
                <li>Heads-up display (HUD), sunroof, wireless charger, reverse parking camera, cooled glovebox, 360° camera on top trims</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Venue</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>8″ or 10.25″ touchscreen with Bluelink connected car tech, sunroof, ambient lighting, auto AC, voice command, air purifier, 7-speaker Bose system (top trims), dual dash cameras (O and IRVM-mounted) in N Line</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="verdict">
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Edge:</span> Venue edges out when it comes to connectivity and premium features, while Brezza offers sufficient essentials with modern appeal.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">7.Ride & Handling</h2>
            
            <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
            <p>MacPherson strut front, torsion beam rear—comfort-focused ride for Indian roads. SHVS mild-hybrid delivers smooth low-end torque.</p>

            <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Venue</h3>
            <p>Similar suspension layout; turbo petrol and diesel variants feel peppier. Bluelink drive modes (Eco/Normal/Sport) enhance handling engagement.</p>

            <div class="verdict">
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Summary:</span> Brezza aims for soft comfort. Venue has a slightly sharper ride, with better mid-range drive quality especially in turbo/diesel trims.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">8.Price Comparison</h2>
            
            <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Brezza</h3>
            <p>Ex-showroom: ₹8.19L — ₹13.88L</p>

            <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Venue</h3>
            <p>Ex-showroom: ₹7.94L — ₹13.62L for standard trims; N Line from ₹12.14L</p>

            <div class="verdict">
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Insight:</span> Prices slightly overlap. Venue's base variants are competitively priced while Brezza sits higher with CNG/mild-hybrid addition. N-Line and diesel variants sit at premium end.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">Final Verdict: Who Should Choose Which?</h2>
            <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                <table class="comparison-table-content">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th class="text-center">Priority</th>
                            <th class="text-center">Choose Maruti Brezza</th>
                            <th class="text-center">Choose Hyundai Venue</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr class="compare-head-text">
                            <td>Fuel efficiency (petrol/CNG)</td>
                            <td>✅ Best-in-class petrol & CNG mileage</td>
                            <td>⚠️ Good diesel, petrol average</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Engine choice</td>
                            <td>⚠️ Only 1.5L petrol + CNG</td>
                            <td>✅ NA petrol, turbo, diesel options</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="compare-head-text">
                            <td>Comfort & ride smoothness</td>
                            <td>✅ Soft, city-oriented ride</td>
                            <td>⚠️ Firmer, fuel/progress boosts</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Tech & convenience features</td>
                            <td>✅ HUD, wireless charger</td>
                            <td>✅ Bluelink, air purifier, Bose, sunroof</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="compare-head-text">
                            <td>Safety systems</td>
                            <td>✅ Core safety (6 airbags, ESP)</td>
                            <td>✅ Advanced systems (ESC, VSM, HAC)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Best-in-segment price</td>
                            <td>✅ Mild-hybrid/CNG priced well</td>
                            <td>⚠️ Broader variants; slightly more expensive</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="compare-head-text">
                            <td>After-sales network</td>
                            <td>✅ Maruti's massive service reach</td>
                            <td>⚠️ Hyundai service good but fewer centers</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div class="verdict">
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Final Recommendation:</span></p>
                <p><strong>Maruti Brezza</strong> is your perfect city SUV if you prioritize outstanding petrol/CNG mileage, soft ride, reliability, and easy maintenance backed by Maruti's network.</p>
                <p><strong>Hyundai Venue</strong> is ideal if you want more engine options (especially the 1.0L turbo or diesel), deeper tech/trims, and enhanced ride dynamics—especially in premium or N Line variants.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">Quick Comparison Highlights</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engines:</span> Brezza — 1.5L NA (102PS); Venue — 1.2L NA, 1.0L turbo (118PS), 1.5L diesel.</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Mileage (ARAI):</span> Brezza — up to 19.8kmpl petrol, 25.5km/kg CNG; Venue — ~18.3kmpl NA/turbo petrol, ~23.4kmpl diesel.</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Boot:</span> Venue's 350L > Brezza's 328L.</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Safety & Tech:</span> Both have 6 airbags, but Venue includes ESC, HAC, VSM, Bluelink, air purifier.</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Price:</span> Brezza ₹8.19–13.88L; Venue ₹7.94–13.62L (+N Line ₹12.14L onwards).</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
            <h2 class="subheading">Conclusion</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Choose the Brezza</span> if you want effortless day-to-day driving, excellent fuel economy, and minimal upkeep.</li>
                <li><span class="font-weight-700">Opt for the Venue</span> if you desire enhanced performance, connected features, and a broader choice of trim & engine options—even if it comes with a slightly firmer ride and higher cost of upkeep.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="div-line"></div>
